  "prompt": "Who designed the icons commonly used for play, pause, record, rewind and stop?",
  "response": "The icons commonly used for play, pause, record, rewind, and stop were designed by Norman Horowitz in the 1960s during his work with the team at RCA (Radio Corporation of America) for their video tape recorders. These symbols have since become standardized in the audio and video industries and are widely recognized across various media devices and platforms. The design focuses on simplicity and clarity, making these icons easily understandable for users.",
